{"article_id":"nfYXRHO9coDUpLwq","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Job Growth Was Slow And Steady In May ,","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"But Jobless Rate Rose","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"There was modest job growth once again in May","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"even as the nation 's unemployment rate ticked up ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"the Bureau of Labor Statistics reported Friday .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"-- 175,000 jobs were added to public and private payrolls last month , slightly more","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"than economists had expected . -- The jobless rate rose to 7.6 percent from April 's 7.5 percent .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"That rate can rise","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"even as more jobs are added","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"because the size of the labor force has also gone up .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"We 'll have more from the report ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"which was released at 8:30 a.m . ET ,","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"as the morning continues .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"Hit your refresh button","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"to be sure","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"you 're seeing our latest updates .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"`` While more work remains to be done ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"today 's employment report provides further confirmation","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"that the U.S. economy is continuing to recover from the worst downturn since the Great Depression , ''","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"says Alan Krueger , chairman of the Council of Economic Advisers , in a statement","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"sent out by the White House .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"Update at 9:10 a.m . ET .","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"Housing , Consumer Spending Support Growth :","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"`` With a gain of 175,000 jobs in May , the resilient labor market sustained moderate job gains this spring , ''","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"Conference Board economist Kathy Bostjancic says in an email to reporters .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"`` The [ federal ] sequester , along with the negative impact from slowing global trade , are being offset by the continued contribution from the revival in the housing market and stronger consumption . ''","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"According to BLS ,","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"there were 27,700 jobs added at retailers last month .","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"Construction firms added 7,000 jobs .","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"`` Professional and business services '' firms increased employment by 57,000 .","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"`` We 're happy","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"that a few Americans were able to find jobs in the last month ,","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"but millions of unemployed and underemployed Americans are still waiting for the recovery","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"President Obama promised years ago .","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"This is the status quo","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"- well below where our economy needs to be","depth":14},{"id":36,"text":"to grow , ''","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"Republican National Committee Chairman Reince Priebus says in a statement .","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"Update at 9 a.m . ET .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Government Was Only A Slight Drag :","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"While private employers added an estimated 178,000 jobs to their payrolls in May ,","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"government agencies reduced their workforces by 3,000 .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Economists have been watching the government data closely","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"to see how much of an effect federal spending cuts are having on the economy .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Update at 8:55 a.m . ET .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"Why The Jobless Rate Went Up :","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"As we said earlier ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"the jobless rate can go up","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"even as employers say","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"they 've taken on more workers","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"because the size of the labor force has increased more than the number of jobs","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"that were added to payrolls .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"-- There were 420,000 more people in the labor force last month than in April .","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"-- One reason for the growth was that fewer people were counted among the ranks of `` discouraged workers . ''","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"The agency says","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"780,000 people","depth":17},{"id":56,"text":"who wanted to work","depth":17},{"id":57,"text":"had given up looking","depth":16},{"id":58,"text":"because they did n't think","depth":16},{"id":59,"text":"they would find jobs .","depth":16},{"id":60,"text":"That was down from 835,000 in April .","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"Update at 8:45 a.m . ET .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"April Job Growth Revised Down ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"March Revised Up Again :","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"In its initial report about job growth in April , BLS said","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"165,000 jobs had been added to payrolls that month .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"Now , it says","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"the increase was 149,000 .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"But it has also revised up","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"- for the second time -","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"the increase in March .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"Initially , it said","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"that 88,000 jobs were added that month .","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"In its second swipe at that figure , BLS said","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"the increase was 138,000 .","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"Now , it says","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"there were 142,000 more jobs in March than in February .","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"Our original post -","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"`` What Will Jobs Report Say ?","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"Slow Growth Is Best Bet '' :","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"Ahead of Friday morning 's much-anticipated report about the nation 's unemployment rate and how many jobs were","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"( hopefully )","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"added to payrolls in May ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"economists are expecting to hear :","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"-- That the jobless rate was unchanged from April 's 7.5 percent .","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"-- That there were about 170,000 more jobs , a modest increase .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"In other words ,","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"as NPR 's Yuki Noguchi said on Morning Edition ,","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"it 's likely to be a more-of-the-same kind of report .","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"Bloomberg News says","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"U.S. stock futures are little changed","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"as the 8:30 a.m . ET release of the employment news approaches","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"- a sign","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"that the markets are also thinking","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"that the report will be yet another sign","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"that job growth remains sluggish .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"A month ago , the Bureau of Labor Statistics said","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"that 165,000 jobs were added to payrolls in April","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"( a figure","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"that could be revised in Friday 's report ) .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"We 'll update with news from the May report","depth":4},{"id":101,"text":"once it 's released .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":203,"left":103,"right":202,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":103,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":202,"left":177,"right":201,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":177,"left":116,"right":176,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":116,"left":110,"right":115,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":110,"left":107,"right":109,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":105,"